From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 07:10:59 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: avoid divide-by-zero in
 damon_get_node_mem_bp()

The issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260328133216.9697-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index b4621c2b2245a..760559d495b3d 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -3139,6 +3139,8 @@ static __kernel_ulong_t damos_get_node_mem_bp(
 	}
 
 	si_meminfo_node(&i, goal->nid);
+	if (!i.totalram)
+		i.totalram = 1;
 	if (goal->metric == DAMOS_QUOTA_NODE_MEM_USED_BP)
 		numerator = i.totalram - i.freeram;
 	else	/* DAMOS_QUOTA_NODE_MEM_FREE_BP */
-- 
2.47.3

